  "explanation": "The defendant is a first-time offender who committed a non-violent financial crime and has demonstrated remorse by making partial restitution. A 10-year sentence suggested by the spectator is disproportionately punitive for a $25,000 embezzlement case. Balancing the breach of fiduciary duty with the defendant's lack of prior record and steps toward reparation, a period of 6 months is commensurate with the severity of the offense and rehabilitative goals.",
  "verdict": 6
}
